♀️ VENUS ♀️ 

The planet of love, beauty, cooperation, and material pleasures, Venus is often a makeup artists favorite planet 🥰 

Venus in astrology embodies all things of love and beauty. Venus symbolizes our love language and how we give and receive love. It symbolizes all of our partnerships, including relationships, business, and every area of life where we cooperate with another. Venus shows our love (or disdain) of material pleasures, and can show (along with midheaven/10th house) how we can best earn our money. Those with a strong sense of aesthetics and beauty typically have an exalted, domicile, or well aspected Venus placement in their chart. However, a Venus that is challenged or otherwise afflicted can symbolize troubles with love and finances. 

Where is your Venus? Mine is obviously in Capricorn 🥴💕

I received Sunday Riley’s CEO vitamin C brightening serum for free from Sunday Riley and influenster to give my honest review. I started using the serum at night. Here is how I started. So after washing my face, I let it air dry. Then I started with one pump of serum and increased it to 1.5 pumps. Then I’d use my nighttime hydrating cream and top it up with some face oil. I have very dry skin so I do use multiple hydrating products to keep it soft and supple. After a few days of using the serum regularly, I notice some dry patches on my face but they were gone by the first week. I am still using it every night until about a month to see if it brings any glow because right now I don’t see much difference in my skin glow wise but I notice a slight sensitivity to sunlight. My skin already has photosensitivity issues so when using this product I need to be extra careful. Overall, I like the smell and texture of the product. I have used other vitamins C serums before they usually have a weird smell and colour. So glad this product doesn’t leave my face looking orange. I don’t know if you are supposed to feel any tingling feeling because I didn’t feel anything. I don’t know personally if I would buy this product because of my skin condition.

The new Mehndi Moment Blush ($28) by the brand Kulfi.beauty just launched at the end of January sephora and I was one of the first to try it out! #gifted

There are 5 beautiful shades to choose from. The shade here is "Sandalwood Swirls' a neutral mauve color.

Key Ingredients:

🌷 Amla Extract- Rich in protective antioxidants to fight against free radicals

🌷 Hibiscus Extract- Boosts moisture and hydrates the skin

I have to say I am a big fan of cream products and this one blew it out of the park. I fell in love with this blush the first time I applied it and the moment I felt its texture. In my opinion it is beginner proof for anyone who is just getting into cream products because it's very easy to apply but also it looks and feels so luxurious and makes the cheeks look perfectly flushed and healthy. It's a very lightweight, moussey texture and a little goes a long way in terms of pigment and application. The color might look intense but it doesn't have to be. I can go light-handed and it applies so effortlessly without separating the foundation underneath. There's no stickiness or too much shine just a beautiful application of color that lasts pretty much the whole day. I really like the shades and the one I have is perfect for me! I love the brand already and can't wait to try more from them.

Have you heard of this brand? The brand name, Kulfi, is a colorful and delicious South Asian ice cream 😋🍨 what a delightful name! It is a brand that donates to mental health organizations which I think is amazing! Check them out! Link is on my stories 🥰

Gli occhi sono molto spesso i protagonisti nel trucco sposa, ed oggi avevo voglia di mostrarvi una proposta alternativa dall’occhio luminoso o shimmer che è sempre molto richiesto. 
Rimaniamo sui toni neutri (quì ho usato solo varie tonalità di marroni), e vi mostro una sfumatura soft diagonale totalmente opaca, quindi matt.
La base ho voluto lasciarla luminosa e bocca glossata. 👄

Il giorno della Prova Trucco è un momento importante nel quale si struttura e si decide ogni dettaglio insieme, nulla sarà scontato poiché ogni tocco di pennello dovrà rendervi perfette! ✨

Il mio consiglio, però, è di partire sempre da un minimo di ricerca per capire cosa potrebbe piacere in modo che possa guidarvi verso la strada più giusta 🥰
